  "prompt": "How do I prepare myself for Harvard Business school?",
  "response": "To prepare for Harvard Business School (HBS), consider the following steps:\n\n1. Academic Preparation\n- Maintain a strong undergraduate GPA\n- Take challenging courses in business, economics, and analytics\n- Consider taking GMAT/GRE prep courses\n- Aim for a high standardized test score (average GMAT: 730)\n\n2. Professional Experience\n- Gain 3-5 years of high-quality professional experience\n- Seek leadership roles and demonstrate impact\n- Work in diverse industries or roles\n- Build a strong professional network\n\n3. Leadership Development\n- Take on leadership positions at work\n- Participate in community or volunteer leadership roles\n- Develop strong communication and teamwork skills\n\n4. Application Preparation\n- Research HBS's program thoroughly\n- Craft a compelling personal narrative\n- Prepare strong essays highlighting achievements\n- Secure impressive recommendation letters\n- Demonstrate clear career goals\n\n5. Additional Considerations\n- Develop international exposure\n- Learn additional languages\n- Engage in extracurricular activities\n- Stay updated on global business trends\n\n6. Financial Preparation\n- Research financial aid options\n- Plan for tuition and living expenses\n- Consider scholarship opportunities\n\n7. Interview Preparation\n- Practice interviewing skills\n- Be prepared to discuss your experiences\n- Show self-awareness and potential\n\nRemember, HBS seeks well-rounded candidates with exceptional potential.",
